wikipedia_page.main: Henry Paull (1824–1898) was a British Conservative Party politician, and barrister.The son of Archibald Paull of Devonshire Place, Paull entered Middle Temple in 1845, and was appointed Deputy Lieutenant of Middlesex in 1859.With Liberal-Conservative principles, Paull was elected Conservative MP for St Ives at the 1857 general election and held the seat until 1868 when he stood down.
